In Doe v. Brown, 331 S.C. 491, 489 S.E.2d 917 (1997), Baby Girl Ashlie was conceived as the result of Brownâ€™s statutory rape of the twelve-year-old mother.Â  The mother relinquished her parental rights and consented to adoption.Â  Brown, joined by his parents, intervened and opposed the adoption.Â  The family court terminated Brownâ€™s parental rights, and that ruling was affirmed by the supreme court. 

